answers.body_markdown:
This is because you are producing content by the function that used to be replaced with a shortcode. As documented in [Wordpress Codex][1],  The function called by the shortcode should never produce an output of any kind. Shortcode functions should return the text that is to be used to replace the shortcode. Producing the output directly will lead to unexpected results. This is similar to the way filter functions should behave, in that they should not produce expected side effects from the call since you cannot control when and where they are called from.

For example, if you are creating an HTML that needs to be replaced with the shortcode the example return should be like

    $html = &#39;&lt;div class=&quot;test-field&quot;&gt;&#39;;
    $html .= get_field(&#39;test-field&#39;);
    $html .= &#39;&lt;/div&gt;&#39;;
    return $html;

and not like this

    the_field(&#39;test-field&#39;);


  [1]: https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/add_shortcode/

