    }

&gt; Default parameters are not allowed
&gt; 
&gt; in the out-of-class definition of a member of a class template (they have to be provided in the declaration inside the class body).
&gt; Note that member templates of non-template classes can use default
&gt; parameters in their out-of-class definitions (see GCC bug 53856)

 (https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/template_parameters)

